.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "Holberton School" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic command line interpreter that reads input from the user, parses it, and executes commands.

It supports simple, one-word commands that match the full path of executables.

.SH USAGE
Upon running
.B simple_shell
, the program will prompt the user with "> ", waiting for a command.

Only commands that are given as full paths (e.g., /bin/ls) are allowed.

.SH EXAMPLES
Run the shell:
.RS
$ ./hsh
.RE

Execute a command:
.RS
> /bin/ls
.RE

